The American broadcast standard for FM pre-emphasis is 75 uS.
The European (and most everyone else) is 50 uS.

As a result, most German radios tend to sound different when
used in the US, even if they were &quot;export models.&quot;

I've been gathering up test equipmeent for the past year to
have a detailed look at the audio of several FM radios to
see if I can quantify exactly what's going on between the
detector and my ears.

I would expect a certain amount of low and high frequency
increase or roll off, but there appear to be odd peaks in
the bass  that result in a thumping effect on some program
material.

All in all, this should be a fun exercise.

Jeff
