And of course, pre-emphasis serves a purpose.  Boost the highs before
sending, so then at the receiving end when you filter it back to normal
you also knock out the obnoxious high frequency noise.  If you didn't boost
in the first place, then the filtering would alter the signal along
with taking out the unwanted background noise.

I think the concept gets a bit lost when they talk in terms of uS
pre-emphasis, since it doesn't immediately represent frequency.  50uS
is the invert of a higher frequency than the invert of 75uS.

Michael
